results.definition: a sudden and decisive increase
examples: a jump in attendance

results.definition: an abrupt transition
examples: a successful leap from college to the major leagues

results.definition: (film) an abrupt transition from one scene to another
a sudden involuntary movement
examples: he awoke with a start

results.definition: descent with a parachute
examples: he had done a lot of parachuting in the army

results.definition: the act of jumping; propelling yourself off the ground
examples: he advanced in a series of jumps
the jumping was unexpected

results.definition: move forward by leaps and bounds
examples: The horse bounded across the meadow
The child leapt across the puddle
Can you jump over the fence?

results.definition: move or jump suddenly, as if in surprise or alarm
examples: She startled when I walked into the room

results.definition: make a sudden physical attack on
examples: The muggers jumped the woman in the fur coat

results.definition: increase suddenly and significantly
examples: Prices jumped overnight

results.definition: be highly noticeable
enter eagerly into
examples: He jumped into the game

results.definition: rise in rank or status

results.definition: jump down from an elevated point

the widow leapt into the funeral pyre

results.definition: run off or leave the rails

bypass
